title: Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1979-09-05
description:
Set 1: 	Mississippi Half-Step Uptown Toodeloo > Franklin's Tower ; Mama Tried > Mexicali Blues ; Peggy-O ; Cassidy ; Loser ; The Promised Land

Set 2:	Scarlet Begonias > Fire On The Mountain ; Estimated Prophet > Eyes Of The World > Drums > Space > Black Peter ; I Need A Miracle > Bertha > Good Lovin'

Encore:	U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
I've Tried To Find Reasons NOT To Give This Five Stars But I can't.  

OK, OK.  So Half-Step is not perfect (which I love as an opener) with Jerry trying to find his way vocally (god, that January laryngitis ruined him throughout '79) and  Eyes is a little too fast (you are correct njpg, but that can be fixed in editing); and ol' Jer is still having his troubles singing his way through Black Peter but... DAMN - the show's line-up is killer on paper.  Just look at it!   I can't say this is an "X" Factor show with The Boyz being workman-like more than inspired, which makes it hard to give this a solid, unquestionable five.  But there isn't a bad song in the bunch, played reasonably well - especially in the second set.  And Barry's recording is beautiful.  I mean "sweet spot" beautiful: high off the crowd and warm & fuzzy.  You can't ask for much more.  

IMHO, this is one of the best examples of the band's professionalism, simply going through the motions of putting on a great show.  Many times I read "going through the motions" as being taken negatively.  In this case, "going through the motions" is seeing, or in this case hearing, just how good these guys were on a night when that etherial spark of magic and one-ness with the crowd and the universe wasn't there.  Practice really does make perfect.  Because in this case, not being just exactly perfect, they overcame a moment in time that is not otherworldly, "X" Factor fabulous.  

But that doesn't mean the whole package is worthy of only a better-than-average four stars (yeah, I noticed some folks are calling this a 4.5 show (with good reason)).  Song selection certainly helped this reviewer's opinion.  And with how well it's been recorded by Mr. Glassberg, and the Garcia Cringe-O-Meter not bouncing around too much tonight, I'm reasonably comfortable sneaking in a five.

show gains steam all the way through lotta energy at msg; awesome good lovin' with bobby and jerry extra effort vip's. 

this show rates 4+ but not quite 5...

- They were on their way to a 5 before they butchered Eyes by trying to play it faster than they could, which they did a lot post-78 and pre-87. I HATE rushed Eyes. It's like, "can you guys not hear yourselves falling off the beat? Slow down!"
